sentences: Tucker joined the Athens, Georgia-based Drive-By Truckers in 2003, replacing original bassist Earl Hicks.
She played bass on their next two records, The Dirty South and A Blessing and a Curse, before contributing her first songs on 2008's Brighter Than Creation's Dark.
Patterson Hood announced Tucker's departure from the band in December 2011 via a post on the band's Facebook page.

The band released their first album A Tell All in October 2013, a record that features songs "about love and jealousy, nights spent on the road and nights spent in the kitchen, the things men do to women and women do for men."
Hood stated that "Her charm and spark will be irreplaceable and her part in our last decade of this band's history is indisputable."
Tucker had previously played upright bass on the Truckers' album Decoration Day.
